# Documentation & Spellcheck

## Hugo site (`docs/`)

The documentation site is a Hugo project rendered to `docs/public/`
(ignored). Pages live under `docs/content/<section>/<page>.md` and follow
Hugo's content conventions.

### Frontmatter

Every content page begins with YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
title: "Anti-Patterns"
weight: 30                 # ordering within the section
description: "Short summary used in nav previews"
---
```

Order matters — `weight` controls sidebar order. Don't renumber every page
when you add a new one; bump by 10s (`10`, `20`, `30`) so insertions
remain cheap.

### Internal links

Use Hugo-style absolute paths so the site builds correctly under its base
URL: `[Anti-Patterns](/improve/anti-patterns/)`. Trailing slashes
matter — keep them. The [@AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) documentation index
must stay in sync when you add or rename a page.

### Tone & voice

- Cursor-first. Refer to "Cursor", "Cursor IDE", "Cursor agent mode",
  "Cursor rules", not generic "AI tool" copy and never another vendor.
- Second person ("you"), present tense, short sentences.
- Concrete numbers and examples beat adjectives.
- Use `--` for em-dashes in prose; tables use `|` separators with
  one-space padding.
- Code blocks get language tags (` ```typescript`, ` ```bash`).

### Pages that touch features

When you add or rename a webview page (`page-*.ts`), update the matching
page under `docs/content/`. The mapping is usually one-to-one and the
docs are read by both humans and the chat participant when answering
"how do I…" questions.

## `cspell.json`

`npm run spellcheck` runs cspell over the repo using
[@cspell.json](mdc:cspell.json). Custom dictionaries live in the `words`
array (kebab-cased lowercase entries).

When CI fails on spell:

1. **Is it a real misspelling?** Fix the prose.
2. **Is it a real product / proper noun?** Add it to `words` in
   `cspell.json`. Keep the list roughly alphabetical when convenient;
   exact ordering is not enforced.
3. **Is it a CamelCase symbol?** It's already covered by the
   `/[A-Z][a-z]+[A-Z][a-zA-Z]+/` regex in `ignoreRegExpList` — no
   change needed.
4. **Is it inside backticks?** Already covered by `/`[^`]+`/`.

Do not silence spellcheck with inline `cspell:ignore` comments unless a
word genuinely cannot be added to the dictionary (e.g. one-off hash in a
log line). Adding to the dictionary is the default.

### Words you should NOT add

- Stale brand names from harnesses we no longer support beyond what is
  already in the dictionary. (`copilot`, `codex`, `opencode` are
  grandfathered for historical references; do not add `claude`,
  `gemini`, `xcode`, etc. — that would let stale copy slip past
  review.)
